cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the generation and presentation of user profiles, which involves topics of interest and expertise. This falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of semantic layout modes, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of user consumption of the presented information, which could be relevant to the field of cyberpsychology (cs.CY).
